.TH man 3 "11 November 2023" "1.0" "rlibint man page (reddlibc)"
.SH NAME
rlibint, intobinary
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <rlibint.h>

.B void intobinary(unsigned int nbr, unsigned int length);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B intobinary()
.R function convert an unsigned int into binary and prints it. It takes:

.B \t nbr:
.R An unsigned int to convert to binary

.B \t length:
.R The max length of the binary number that will be printed. (If > 30, it will default to 30)

.SH NOTES
When including this header, make sure to link reddlibc.a (in /usr/lib/ on default reddlibc installs) when compiling.
.SH SEE ALSO
rlibstr(3), rlibinput(3), rlibchar(3), rlibstdio(3)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs. Although some consider that they are a feature in C.
